<article>
<strong>Binary numbers</strong> are made up of two digits 1 and 0, this is known as <strong>base two system</strong> or <strong>binary system.</strong>
<br>
<br>
(i)	 Convert 17 to binary number
<br>
(ii) Convert 111<sub>2</sub> to base ten.
<br>
<br>
<%= image_tag 'base2conv1.png', alt:'base-2-conversion1 image', class: 'carol col-12 ml-4' %>
<br>
<i><%= link_to "Click here for more information on the conversion of number bases.", page18_path, class: "text-danger"%></i>
<br>
<strong>Example 1</strong>
<br>
Find the value of (1011<sub>2</sub>)<sup>2</sup>. Leave the answer in base two.
<br>
<br>
<strong>Solution</strong>
<br>
<strong>Step 1; Convert 1011<sub>2</sub> to base ten:</strong>
<br>
<strong><i>3 2 1 0 – powers</i></strong>
<br>
1 0 1 1<sub>2</sub> = 1 x 23 + 0 x 22 + 1 x 21 + 1 x 20
<br>
       = 1 x 8 + 0 x 4 + 1 x 2 + 1 x 1
       <br>
       = 8 + 0 + 2 + 1
       <br>
       =  11
       <br>
1 0 1 1<sub>2</sub> = 11 or 11<sub>10</sub>
<br>
<br>
<strong>Step 2; Find the square of 11:</strong>
<br>
The square of 11 = 11<sup>2</sup>  = <strong>121</strong>
<br>
<br>
<strong>Step 3; Convert 121 to base two;</strong>
<br>
<%= image_tag 'convert121tobase2.png', alt:'convert121tobase2 image', class: 'carol col-12 ml-4' %>
<br>
<span class = 'ml-5'>(1011<sub>2</sub>)<sup>2</sup>  => <strong>1111001<sub>2</sub></strong></span>
<br>
<br>
<strong>Note;</strong> in the next topic you will learn how to solve the above question in one step.
<div class="d-flex justify-content-center mt-3">
<h2 class='text-dark justify-content-center'>Operations with Binary Numbers</h2>
</div>
It is possible to add, subtract and multiply binary numbers the same way we operate with base ten numbers.
<div class="d-flex justify-content-center mt-3">
<h3 class='text-dark justify-content-center'>Operation Rules</h3>
</div>
<strong>Addition;</strong>
<br>
<strong class='text-danger'>0 + 0 = 0;  1 + 0 = 1;  0 + 1 = 1 and  1 + 1 = 10</strong>
<br>
<br>
<strong>Multiplication;</strong>
<br>
<strong class='text-danger'>0 x 0 = 0;  1 x 0 = 0;  0 x 1 = 0;  and 1 x 1 = 1 </strong>
<div class="d-flex justify-content-center mt-3">
<h3 class='text-dark justify-content-center'>Addition in Binary System</h3>
</div>
Add the following (i) 1011<sub>2</sub> + 1101<sub>2</sub> (ii) 101<sub>2</sub> + 111<sub>2</sub> + 101<sub>2</sub>
<br>
<br>
<strong>Solution</strong>
<br>
<br>
(i)
<br>
<strong>Steps;</strong>
<br>
<strong>In 1st column; 1 + 1 = 10; write down 0 and keep 1</strong>
<br>
<strong>In 2nd column; 1 + 0 = 1 + 1(kept) = 10; write down 0 and keep 1</strong>
<br>
<strong>In 3rd column; 0 + 1 = 1 + 1(kept) = 10; write down 0 and keep 1</strong>
<br>
<strong>In 4th column; 1 + 1 = 10 + 1(kept) = 11; write down the 11.</strong>
<br>
<%= image_tag 'binaryAddition.png', alt:'binaryaddition image', class: 'carol col-12 ml-4' %>
<br>
<br>
(ii)
<br>
<strong>Steps;</strong>
<br>
<strong>In 1st column; 1 + 1 = 10; 10 + 1 = 11; write down 1 and keep 1</strong>
<br>
<strong>In 2nd column; 0 + 1 = 1; 1 + 0 = 1; 1 + 1(kept) = 10; write down 0 and keep 1</strong>
<br>
<strong>In 3rd column; 1 + 1 = 10; 10 + 1 = 11; 11 + 1(kept) = 100; write down the 100</strong>
<br>
<%= image_tag 'binaryaddition2.png', alt:'binaryaddition2 image', class: 'carol col-12 ml-4' %>
<div class="d-flex justify-content-center mt-3">
<h3 class='text-dark justify-content-center'>Subtraction in Binary System</h3>
</div>
<strong>Example 1</strong>
<br>
Subtract the following (i) 1110<sub>2</sub> ─ 101<sub>2</sub> (ii) 10100<sub>2</sub> ─ 1110<sub>2</sub>
<br>
<br>
<strong>Solution</strong>
<br>
<br>
(i)
<br>
<strong>Steps;</strong>
<br>
<strong>In 1st column; taking away 1 from 0 is impossible, move 1 from 2nd column to 1st column; 10 ─ 1 = 1 or 2 ─ 1; write down 1</strong>
<br>
<strong>In 2nd column; the 1 in 2nd has been removed leaving 0; 0  ─ 0 = 0; write down 0</strong>
<br>
<strong>In 3rd column; 1 ─ 1 = 0; write down 0</strong>
<br>
<strong>In 4th column; 1 ─ 0 = 1; write down 1</strong>
<%= image_tag 'binarysubtraction.png', alt:'binarysubtarction1 image', class: 'carol col-12 ml-4' %>
<br>
<br>
(ii)
<br>
<strong>Steps;</strong>
<br>
<strong>In 1st column; 0 ─ 0 = 0; write down 0</strong>
<br>
<strong>In 2nd column; taking away 1 from 0 is impossible, move 1 from 3rd column to 2nd column;</strong>
<br>
<strong>10 ─ 1 = 1 or 2 ─ 1 = 1; write down 1</strong>
<br>
<strong>In 3rd column;  1 in 3rd column has been removed leaving 0, taking away 1 from 0 is impossible, move 1 from 5th column to 4th then to 3rd column; 10 – 1 = 1 or 2 ─ 1 = 1; write down 1.</strong>
<br>
<strong>In 4th column; 1 is left in the 4th column (from; 2 ─ 1 as a result of movement of 1 from 5th column); 1 ─ 1 = 0; there is no need to write this 0.</strong>
<br>
<strong>In 5th column; 1 has been removed from this column, leaving 0; there is no need to write this 0.</strong>
<%= image_tag 'binarysubtraction2.png', alt:'binarysubtarction2 image', class: 'carol col-12 ml-4' %>
