</div>
Binary system is generally used in computing such as; <strong>binary system code, punch tape</strong> and <strong>punch cards.</strong>
<br>
<br>
<strong>Cards</strong> are used to store information about events or people. Cards use a binary system of a hole punched out to represent (0) or a slot cut out to represent (1).
<br>
<br>
The card sketched below shows food eaten by a student, Simon Stone;
<br>
<%= image_tag 'punchcard.png', alt:'Punch-card image', class: 'carol col-12 ml-4' %>
<br>
<strong>Example 1</strong>
<br>
(i)	What is the number for the food eaten by Simon Stone?
<br>
(ii)	Which food were eaten by students whose cards represent the following  numbers?
<br>
(a)	1001
<br>
(b)	1101
<br>
(c)	0010
<br>
(d)	1011
<br>
<br>
<strong>Solution</strong>
<br>
(i)
<br>
Food eaten by student(s) => <strong>1</strong>
<br>
Food not eaten by student(s) => <strong>0</strong>
<br>
The number for the food eaten by <strong>Simon Stone;</strong>
<br>
Simon Stone did not eat rice => 0
<br>
Simon Stone ate beans => 1
<br>
Simon Stone ate yam => 1
<br>
Simon Stone did not eat bread => 0
<br>
The number for the food eaten by Simon Stone => <strong>0110</strong> i.e. Beans and Yam.
<br>
<br>
(ii)
<br>
(a)	1001 ate; <strong>rice and bread</strong>
<br>
(b)	1101 ate; <strong>rice, beans and bread</strong>
<br>
(c)	0010 ate; <strong>yam</strong>
<br>
(d)	1011 ate; <strong>rice, yam and bread</strong>
