<strong>Number bases</strong> is the system of total counting of digits used to express numbers in a number system e.g. base two system (binary system) uses only 2 digits; 0 and 1, base-six system uses 6 digits; 0 to 5 and base-ten system uses 10 digits; 0 to 9. The number bases make use of powers of a particular number system i.e. base-ten system is based on powers of 10 and base-six system is based on powers of 6.
<br>
<br>
The most common number system worldwide is <strong>base-ten system</strong>. <strong>Binary system</strong> is also important due to its numerous applications to computing. A computer contains a large number of switches; each switch is either ‘On’ or ‘Off’;
<br>
‘On’ switch => <strong>1</strong>
<br>
‘Off’ switch => <strong>0</strong>
