  <h3 class='text-dark justify-content-center'>Conversion from Base Ten to other Number Bases</h3>
  </div>
  Conversion from base ten to other number bases involves dividing the number in base ten system by the number of the desired base e.g. conversion from base ten to base two means dividing the number in base ten by two and take the record of the remainders. 
  <br>
  Base ten numbers are commonly written as; 22 => 22<sub>10</sub> or 22<sub>ten</sub> , 85 => 85<sub>10</sub> or 85<sub>ten</sub>  etc.
  <br>
  <br>
<strong>Rules for converting from base ten to other base;</strong>
<br>
(i)	Divide the base ten number by the desired base number.
<br>
(ii) Continue to divide until zero (0) is reached, write down any remainder each time.
<br>
(iii) Start at the last remainder and read upwards to get the new number in the desired base.  
<br>
<strong>Example 1</strong>
<br>
(i) Convert 733 and 76 to base five (ii) convert 5046 and 128 to base eight (iii) convert 27 and 18 to base two (iv) convert 725 and 31 to base six
